TITLE: Adding a Dataset with File to a VitessceConfig in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to add a dataset to a Vitessce configuration and attach a data file with its type and coordination values. The example adds a CSV file containing cell coordinates.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vitessce/vitessce/blob/main/sites/docs/docs/view-config-js.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { VitessceConfig, DataType as dt, FileType as ft } from 'vitessce';

const vc = new VitessceConfig({ schemaVersion: "1.0.15", name: "My config" });
const dataset = vc.addDataset("My dataset")
    .addFile({
        url: "http://example.com/my-cell-coordinates.csv",
        fileType: ft.OBS_LOCATIONS_CSV,
        coordinationValues: { obsType: 'cell' },
    });
```

