TITLE: Adding Views to a VitessceConfig in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to add visualization views to a Vitessce configuration. The example adds both a spatial view and a scatterplot view with a specific embedding mapping.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vitessce/vitessce/blob/main/sites/docs/docs/view-config-js.md#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { VitessceConfig, ViewType as vt } from 'vitessce';

const vc = new VitessceConfig({ schemaVersion: "1.0.15", name: "My config" });
const dataset = vc.addDataset("My dataset");
const v1 = vc.addView(dataset, vt.SPATIAL);
const v2 = vc.addView(dataset, vt.SCATTERPLOT, { mapping: "X_umap" });
```

