TITLE: CoordinationType Usage Example in Vitessce Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the CoordinationType constant when linking views in a Vitessce configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vitessce/vitessce/blob/main/sites/docs/docs/constants.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { VitessceConfig, ViewType as vt, CoordinationType as ct } from 'vitessce';

const vc = new VitessceConfig({ schemaVersion: "1.0.15", name: "My config" });
const dataset = vc.addDataset("My dataset");
const v1 = vc.addView(dataset, vt.SPATIAL);
const v2 = vc.addView(dataset, vt.SPATIAL);
vc.linkViews(
    [v1, v2],
    [ct.SPATIAL_ZOOM, ct.SPATIAL_TARGET_X, ct.SPATIAL_TARGET_Y],
    [2, 0, 0]
);
```

